  "local_port": 51788,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much should I aim in my graduation to get into IIM A/B/C assuming I get a 99+ percentile in CAT?",
  "response": "Getting into the top IIMs \u2014 IIM Ahmedabad (A), IIM Bangalore (B), and IIM Calcutta (C) \u2014 requires a strong overall profile, including a high CAT percentile, academic performance, work experience (if applicable), and diversity factors. While a 99-plus percentile in CAT is an excellent starting point, your graduation score (or academic performance) also plays a significant role in the selection process.\n\n### Academic Performance:\n- **Graduation Score**: The top IIMs assign significant weight to your academic performance, especially in Class X, Class XII, and graduation. \n- **Minimum Requirement**: While there is no strict cutoff, candidates with a **minimum of 60%** in graduation (or equivalent CGPA) are generally eligible. However, to be competitive for IIM A/B/C, aiming for **85% or higher** in graduation is advisable.\n- **Consistency**: Consistent academic performance (i.e., strong scores in Class X, Class XII, and graduation) is preferred. Weakness in one area can be offset by strength in others, but a strong graduation score is crucial.\n\n### Selection Process:\nThe selection process at IIM A/B/C consists of multiple stages:\n1. **CAT Score**: A 99+ percentile is essential to clear the initial cutoff.\n2. **Written Ability Test (WAT) and Personal Interview (PI)**: Your graduation score and overall academic profile will be evaluated during this stage.\n3. **Composite Score**: The final selection is based on a composite score that includes:\n   - CAT score (weightage: 20-30%)\n   - Academic performance (weightage: 20-30%)\n   - Work experience (if applicable)\n   - Diversity factors (gender, academic background, etc.)\n\n### Tips:\n- If your graduation score is below 85%, focus on excelling in other areas like:\n  - Strong performance in Class X and XII.\n  - Significant work experience or achievements (if applicable).\n  - Exceptional performance in WAT and PI.\n- If you\u2019re still pursuing graduation, aim for the highest possible score to strengthen your profile.\n\n### Summary:\nAim for **85% or higher** in graduation to maximize your chances of getting into IIM A/B/C, along with a 99+ percentile in CAT and a well-rounded profile.",
